      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this way. Losing someone after a decade is a devastating blow, and the way your mind flickers between memory and forgetting is a heavy, painful cycle to carry every single day. Please know that your feelings are valid, and you don't have to do this alone.\n\nWhile I can't take the weight of your grief away, I can offer a perspective that might help you navigate this morning. Sometimes, the mind is just trying to protect itself from the sharp edges of loss, and it needs time to heal.\n\nIf you are feeling like you can't do another morning like this, please consider reaching out to a mental health professional or a support group who specializes in grief. They can provide a safe space to talk about your feelings and help you find new ways to cope. You are not alone in this journey, and there are people who want to support you through these difficult times.",
